Description: Chios Global helps its clients solve legal disputes by connecting them with suitable attorneys.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: What We Do We guide companies outside the United States through the intricate U.S. legal system by quickly analyzing their legal needs then identifying preeminent attorneys with the right skills to best address the specific issue.   We then typically stay on the matter as our client's personal advocate, interfacing with outside counsel and providing input on all strategic decisions and ensuring that legal spend is kept to a minimum. How We Do It  Our principals are all licensed attorneys with decades of experience in private practice at some of the largest U.S. business law firms and as senior in-house counsel at a prominent global investment manager. Each member of our team has a diverse background in international business and commercial law – from corporate matters, asset sales, acquisitions, and expansion – to litigation, dispute resolution, and mediation.  Our mission is to remove the exclusive control that law firms have over their client, which only benefits their firm.   We find the right professionals for our clients' needs without alliances to any specific firm. This prevents our clients from paying unnecessary legal fees, and they only get services they need.   What It Costs   The question on everyone’s mind.  Our job is to reduce legal spend, not increase it.  We charge a nominal fee to consult with your company and get up to speed. After that, we generally charge a one-time small transparent flat fee. No surprises or hidden costs.  And we usually pay for ourselves right away through immediate savings from outside counsel you would not receive without us.  We have never lost a client due to our cost – only gained them.

Description: Creator of the SipLink spontaneous meetup app, that enables people with common interests to chat, meet and build real friendships.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: SipLink is a spontaneous meetup app that makes it easier for people with common interests to chat, meet and build friendships.  SipLink works by users submitting location sensitive posts. Posts represent a variety of conversation topics.  Some ways people are using SipLink are: - Your best friend lives far away? Find someone with common interest in your neighborhood that you can talk to. - New in town? Find a friend who could help you to integrate into the new environment. - Looking for your soulmate? Your SipLink profile is more than just a face shot. Have meaningful conversations in the safe confines of your favorite coffee shop. - Looking for a playdate? Find other moms and dads in your neighborhood. - Trying to learn a new language? Find fellow language speakers locally and practice together at your favorite coffee shop. - International? SipLink allows you to find and connect with your compatriots locally. - Looking for a study partner? Use SipLink to connect and study at your local coffee shop. - Are you a freelancer? Use SipLink to connect with potential clients at coffee shop you prefer to work out of. - Interested in board games? Find partners to play with at local coffee shops. Main features of the application: 1. Post to start conversations with other SipLink users What is it that you want to talk about? Creating new posts lets other people know what interests you at this moment. Since your new posts will be immediately visible to other people in your local area, adding posts is the best way to start the process of making connections within the app. When you add a post, you can select the coffee shop that you would like to meet at and you can say what is on your mind. You can also skip specifying a coffee shop in which case the post will originate from your approximate current location. 2. Browse nearby posts from people looking to meet over coffee Nearby posts lets you see what people are interested in talking about in your local area. By browsing posts you will be able to find people you may want to meet. The most recent and geographically closest posts are displayed to you. You can scroll down to see older posts and you can use pull down refresh to see new post activity. When you add your own posts they will be immediately visible to other people in your local area.  Each post shows you: some details about the user who made the post; the coffee shop where they would like to meet, its address and distance from you; when the post was made and what the person is looking to talk about.  3. Check profiles of people you could meet By entering profile information about yourself you give other people an idea who you are and what your interests may be. By browsing the profiles of other people you can learn more about them, which will help you decide if chatting with them or meeting at your local coffee shop would be worthwhile. In the profiles view, you can: add pictures to your profile; specify information about yourself; and specify your name and age. 4. Chat with people Chatting with other users within SipLink is a convenient way to meet new people. For example, if you see a post that is interesting, you can chat with the person who made the post. Chatting with other users within SipLink is a convenient way to coordinate when and where you might meet. For example, you would like to meet a person who made a given post so you chat with them to work out the details of at which coffee shop and what time to meet. Chatting with other users within SipLink is a convenient way to maintain connections you have made. For example, you have connected with several people through SipLink and you can chat with them to plan future meetings or simply to touch base or keep your conversation going.

Description: Self Storage marketplace creator
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: RovingBox.com enables homeowners to earn money by renting out the extra space in their garage, attic or basement to people whom need extra storage space. RovingBox has launched a service to benefit those who find traditional self-storage options too inflexible and expensive. The RovingBox website (www.rovingbox.com) helps match local homeowners whom have unused storage space in their garage, attic or basement with people who need storage space for their personal items.       "RovingBox provides a great way for homeowners to earn passive income by simply renting out a corner of their garage to people who need storage space for their stuff.  For the homeowner it makes good financial sense, and renters benefit by having a storage space that is often more affordable and flexible than they’d otherwise get by signing a lease on a traditional storage unit." says Zachary Price, Co-founder of RovingBox. “With the rise of the new ‘Sharing Economy’ we saw that the Self-Storage industry could use a makeover. Our service upends traditional self-storage business models by creating a marketplace where people can list and rent unused space. We are excited to help homeowners to make extra money every month, while providing would-be renters with inexpensive and environmentally friendly storage options in their neighborhood.” How RovingBox.com works is simple. All homeowners have to do is create a listing on RovingBox.com which includes photos and a description of the space for rent, plus and what their "House Rules" are (what a renter is able to store and when they can access their stored goods). Those needing storage or parking can search the RovingBox for storage options in their area and then request a booking. The space owner is then able to review the request and discuss all details and concerns with the renter before confirming the request. Getting paid is easy; once the home owner just accepts the offer and the renter moves their things into the space, RovingBox charges the renter’s credit card and deposits the rent payments into the homeowners banking or PayPal account.  To establish security and maintain trust between renters and homeowners, RovingBox.com offers: •	A public rating system on which RovingBox customers rate each other based on a set of criteria. •	A messaging system that enables people to chat and get to know each other before confirming a space rental. The system is also used for requesting rental space access. •	A three-day refund guarantee. A renter can get his or her money refunded even after making a booking if he or she does not feel comfortable with the renter or the space itself after the first contact.  Please visit http://www.rovingbox.com for more information.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Real Estate

Description: Navy Movers is a moving company specifically concentrating on assisting military members move their families from base to base.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Navy Movers has been helping military men and women and their families for over 15 years with personalized moving services as well as convenient storage and automobile transport worldwide. We specialize in making secure moves happen quickly and we have moved thousands of military personnel to and from military bases as well as off base housing in states all across America as well as overseas. No matter where you need to go and how long you have to get there, we’ve got you covered from start to finish to ensure that your next move will be convenient and handled fast so that you will not have any downtime to prevent you from being where you have to be. Our moving trucks and other equipment are all carefully maintained and up to date with GPS tracking installed so that you are able to keep track of your property as it is moved from one location to another. We also offer the best storage options nationwide and guarantee that all storage offered is secure and clean at all times. Navy Movers has many options for moving whether you plan to pack on your own time or have us handle everything from packing all the way through delivery and getting everything unloaded and moved into the new place. We work fast and make sure everything is handled efficiently so that you will be moved in as fast as possible. We know that moving is stressful and our mission is to get you moved with as little stress as possible so that you can sit back and relax while we take care of everything.
